4cn.title: Transposition (as an element of a symmetric group)
4cn.clickbait: A transposition is the simplest kind of permutation: it swaps two elements.
4cn.text:
In a [-497], a transposition is a permutation which has the effect of swapping two elements while leaving everything else unchanged.
More formally, it is a permutation of [order_of_a_group_element order] $2$ which fixes all but two elements.

%%%knows-requisite([4cg]):
A transposition is precisely an element with cycle type $2$.
%%%

# Example

In $S_5$, the permutation $(12)$ is a transposition: it swaps $1$ and $2$ while leaving all three of the elements $3,4,5$ unchanged.
However, the permutation $(124)$ is not a transposition, because it has order $3$, not order $2$.
